Parts of the skip's narrative ended up as little hints and implications, which is hilarious in hindsight since I pretty much need to be whacked over the head by a baseball bat shaped like the story to get an article.

Essentially, the little strike-out at the end is meant to imply that it's affecting a new person now - Katherine Tindall, and it's using that to make itself Thaumiel. I personally headcanon that the app's previous actions were trying to push Zhou up the Foundation by encouraging them to take the promotion, but when they stopped being cooperative it made them out to be crazy so it could be reassigned to a new researcher  but that's all up to interpretation, I suppose. A lot of the stuff here I tried to keep kind of murky.




Anyways, thanks for reading!





